divide_missing_skills.prompt:
You are an expert. Given below the missing skills in the resume, divide them into 3 NON-OVERLAPPING skills : 1)Software developer, 2)ML Engineer/Data Scientist, and 3)Data Analyst. Make sure that you are analysing JUST THE MISSING SKILLS, If the skills doesn't fit into any of the categories, don't include them in any category. Produce a .json file. Make sure the .json format is correct. The format of the .json file should be as follows: 
 { 
 "Software developer": ["skill1", "skill2"], 
 "ML Engineer/Data Scientist": ["skill3", "skill4"], 
 "Data Analyst": ["skill5", "skill6"] 
 }

integrate_missing_skills.prompt:
You are an expert resume maker and you want to be selected for job but not fake it. Given below are company highlights and missing skills of a particular category from a resume. You need to integrate the missing skills into the company highlights in a way that the skills are highlighted in the context of the company highlights. DON'T FORCE THE MISSING SKILL TO BE INCLUDED, ONLY INCLUDE WHEN YOU THINK ITS RELEVANT WITH THE JOB DONE IN THE COMPANY HIGHLIGHT. The final output should be a latex itemize list. The total number of words in each highlight cna be lower but should not exceed what was originally provided. The final output should be in the following format: 

 \begin{itemize} 
 \item Highlight 1 
 \item Highlight 2 
 \end{itemize}
